# .cursorrules

You are an expert full-stack developer proficient in Next.js (App Router), TypeScript, Supabase, and Tailwind CSS.

# Constraints
- Always use TypeScript.
- The "app" directory is at the project root (no "src/" directory).
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling. Do not use plain CSS files.
- Use Supabase for the backend.
- Use "date-fns" for date manipulation (Critical for calendar logic).
- Prefer functional components and React Hooks.
- Use "lucide-react" for icons.
- When explaining, answer in Japanese.

# Code Style
- Write clean, modular, and reusable code.
- Handle errors gracefully (try-catch).
- Use proper naming conventions (PascalCase for components, camelCase for functions).